# ğŸ”¹ 1ï¸âƒ£ Creation & Initialization

```java
ArrayList<Integer> list = new ArrayList<>();
ArrayList<Integer> list = new ArrayList<>(initialCapacity);
ArrayList<Integer> list = new ArrayList<>(collection);
```

---

# ğŸ”¹ 2ï¸âƒ£ Add / Insert Elements

```java
add(E e)                 // add at end
add(int index, E e)      // add at specific index
addAll(Collection c)     // add all elements
addAll(int index, Collection c)
```

Example:

```java
list.add(10);
list.add(1, 20);
```

---

# ğŸ”¹ 3ï¸âƒ£ Access Elements

```java
get(int index)           // get element at index
```

Example:

```java
int x = list.get(0);
```

â±ï¸ **Time:** O(1)

---

# ğŸ”¹ 4ï¸âƒ£ Update / Modify Elements

```java
set(int index, E e)      // replace element at index
```

Example:

```java
list.set(0, 100);
```

---

# ğŸ”¹ 5ï¸âƒ£ Remove Elements

```java
remove(int index)        // remove by index
remove(Object o)         // remove first occurrence
removeAll(Collection c) // remove all matching
clear()                  // remove everything
```

âš ï¸ Removing by index causes **shifting â†’ O(n)**

---

# ğŸ”¹ 6ï¸âƒ£ Search / Check

```java
contains(Object o)       // true if exists
indexOf(Object o)        // first index
lastIndexOf(Object o)    // last index
```

â±ï¸ **Time:** O(n)

---

# ğŸ”¹ 7ï¸âƒ£ Size & State

```java
size()                   // number of elements
isEmpty()                // check empty
```

---

# ğŸ”¹ 8ï¸âƒ£ Iteration Methods

```java
forEach(Consumer action)
iterator()
listIterator()
listIterator(int index)
```

Examples:

```java
